dismissalComment.html: the partnership comes to an end! Ervine looks to reverse sweep it and gets a top edge that settles easily in Rahim's gloves. And can you believe the fact that it is the first wicket for spin today!! Shows how well Taibu and Ervine have played the spinners

and the cracks come into play! Good length ball outside the off stump and coming in. Masakadza looks to play across the line and the bounce deceives him. He is struck on the flap of the back pad and the umpire has no hesitation in raising the index finger as Masakadza was playing on the backfoot. As a colleague of mine would say "Plumb as they come"

dismissalComment.html: and Mash has struck again! he has been pretty consistent with his line and length today, this one was slightly angled across the left-hander from just back of a length, it rapped him on the back pad around off stump as he pushed outside the line from the crease, umpire Asoka raised the finger right away, Zimbabwe are in disarray

dismissalText.commentary: Brendan Taylor run out (Sohrawordi Shuvo) 0 (2b 0x4 0x6 2m) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: and a nightmare start! Fuller ball outside the off stump. Taylor opens his arms and drives it to extra-cover. Shuvo moves to his left and fields. He sees that Taylor is half-way down the pitch and throws it to the keeper's end. Rahim need not even lay a finger on it as the throw takes the bails off. Run-out of a free-hit!

dismissalText.commentary: Tamim Iqbal c Cremer b Dabengwa 95 (96b 5x4 7x6 102m) SR: 98.95

dismissalComment.html: gets out in a temptation to go for the eighth. He comes down the track and mistimes a lofted shot into the leg side. Cremer runs in from deep midwicket and dives forward to complete the catch. He was just five runs away from the century. The crowd has been silenced as Tamim is a local boy but what entertainment till it lasted

dismissalComment.html: good length ball on the middle stump. Shakib comes down the track and slogs it straight down the throat of Taylor at long-on. dismissalComment.html: and there's the first blood! Imrul goes for the cut shot with his feet moving nowhere and does not quite reach the ball. As he does not reach the ball properly, he only manages to get an outside edge back to the keeper. Taibu takes it comfortably and the Zimbabwean camp is happy

headshotImage.longCaption: Abdur Razzak player page headshot cutout, 2021

commentTextItems.html: and there's the victory for Bangladesh by six wickets as Rahim pushes it to mid-on for a single

commentPostTextItems.html: After the Tamim hurricane, it was the steady hand of Junaid that saw Bangladesh to the target easily. Tamim has been the difference between the sides today and Bangladesh look in good shape heading into the World Cup. Zimbabwe on the other hand will look towards their top order failing in their duties in this series and would like to fine tune their preparations
Wait on us for the quotes from presentation

Elton Chigumbara says" Very disappointed to lose the game. Bangladesh batted well right through the series and we need to improve our batting. We need to be an altogether different side, in batting when we come for the World Cup"

Shakib Al Hasan " We came back really hard at them. Tamim and Junaid scored runs at the top. Wicket played really well as there was some spin early on. Positive side from the bowling perspective is that fast bowlers are doing well. Crowds kept Tamim going on and hopefully we put up a good show at the World Cup"

Man of the match is Tamim Iqbal who says " I was injured for a few months and needed a few matches to get back. Hundred would have been much better. It doesn't matter if I score a zero or hundred, they(crowd) will love me"
Man of the series is Abdur Razzak
That's it from all of us here and thanks for following us right through the series

As he does not reach the ball properly, he only manages to get an outside edge back to the keeper. Taibu takes it comfortably and the Zimbabwean camp is happy
